tomation must skip PRs already labeled `human-intervention`. That\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:382:continue, per §FS-human-intervention-policy. A PR labeled\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:383:`human-intervention-fixed` is the explicit maintainer signal that manual\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:389:Automated review may add or request the `human-intervention` PR label only when\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:393:infrastructure errors must not be converted into `human-intervention` unless\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:396:(§FS-human-intervention-policy).\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:422:`human-intervention` for these fixable index bucket inconsistencies\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:423:(§FS-human-intervention-policy).\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:440:| `SUCCESS_WITH_INTERVENTION_STATUS` | Tests succeeded after the built-in post-generation recovery modified the working tree (a Codex metadata fix, then Pi removing failing tests as a last resort), and the local CI-equivalent verification (§FS-local-ci-equivalent-verification) passed. The intervention's record is included in the run-metrics and PR description. PR-eligible; distinct from the `human-intervention` label unless §FS-human-intervention-policy separately requires that label. |\n./forge/tests/test_git_worktree_regressions.py:241:                    return_value=\"ai/test/human-intervention/issue-1412\",\n./forge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:351:            forge_metadata.gh(\"issue\", \"edit\", \"2099\", \"--add-label\", \"human-intervention\")\n./forge/tests/test_make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:61:        self.assertIn(\"human-intervention\", labels)\n./forge/tests/test_make_pr_not_for_native_image.py:92:        self.assertIn(\"human-intervention\", create_call)\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:36:HUMAN_INTERVENTION_LABEL = \"human-intervention\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:271:    # human-intervention classification performed by the caller. Library-scoped\n.